        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 5:51PM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 550 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Somerset, or 9 miles north of Poteet, moving northwest at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
San Antonio, Castroville, Leon Valley, Lytle, Somerset, Lacoste,
Lackland AFB, Sea World, Von Ormy, Macdona, Thelma, Mangus Corner,
Espey, and Rossville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
